# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:3847
msgid "Typical command execution uses a shell line sequence as the following."
msgstr "L'excution typique d'une commande utilise une squence de lignes telle que la suivante&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:3848
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ date\n"
"Sun Jun  3 10:27:39 JST 2007\n"
"$ LANG=fr_FR.UTF-8 date\n"
"dimanche 3 juin 2007, 10:27:33 (UTC+0900)"
msgstr ""
"$ date\n"
"Sun Jun  3 10:27:39 JST 2007\n"
"$ LANG=fr_FR.UTF-8 date\n"
"dimanche 3 juin 2007, 10:27:33 (UTC+0900)"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:3852
msgid "Here, the program <literal>date</literal>(1) is executed with different values of the environment variable \"<literal>$LANG</literal>\"."
msgstr "Ici, le programme <literal>date</literal>(1) est excut comme tche d'avant-plan avec diffrentes valeurs de la variable d'environnement &nbsp;<literal>$LANG</literal>&nbsp;."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:3856
msgid "For the first command, \"<literal>$LANG</literal>\" is set to the system default <ulink url=\"&locale;\">locale</ulink> value \"<literal>en_US.UTF-8</literal>\"."
msgstr "Avec la premire commande, &nbsp;<literal>$LANG</literal>&nbsp; est dfinie  la valeur des <ulink url=\"&locale;\">paramtres linguistiques</ulink> par dfaut du systme &nbsp;<literal>en_US.UTF-8</literal>&nbsp;."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:3861
msgid "For the second command, \"<literal>$LANG</literal>\" is set to the French UTF-8 <ulink url=\"&locale;\">locale</ulink> value \"<literal>fr_FR.UTF-8</literal>\"."
msgstr "Avec la deuxime commande, &nbsp;<literal>$LANG</literal>&nbsp; est dfinie  la valeur des <ulink url=\"&locale;\">paramtres linguistiques</ulink> UTF-8 franais &nbsp;<literal>fr_FR.UTF-8</literal>&nbsp;."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:3865
msgid "Most command executions usually do not have preceding environment variable definition.  For the above example, you can alternatively execute as the following."
msgstr "Habituellement, la plupart des excutions de commandes ne sont pas prcdes de la dfinition de variables d'environnement. Pour les exemple ci-dessus, vous pouvez aussi excuter&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:3866
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ LANG=fr_FR.UTF-8\n"
"$ date\n"
"dimanche 3 juin 2007, 10:27:33 (UTC+0900)"
msgstr ""
"$ LANG=fr_FR.UTF-8\n"
"$ date\n"
"dimanche 3 juin 2007, 10:27:33 (UTC+0900)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:3869
msgid "As you can see here, the output of command is affected by the environment variable to produce French output.  If you want the environment variable to be inherited to subprocesses (e.g., when calling shell script), you need to <emphasis role=\"strong\">export</emphasis> it instead by the following."
msgstr "Comme vous pouvez le voir ici, la sortie de la commande est affecte par la variable d'environnement afin que la sortie s'effectue en franais. Si vous dsirez que la variable d'environnement hrite du sous-processus (par exemple le script appelant), vous devrez alors l'<emphasis role=\"strong\">exporter</emphasis> de la manire suivante&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:3870
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ export LANG"
msgstr "$ export LANG"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:3872
msgid "When filing a bug report, running and checking the command under \"<literal>LANG=en_US.UTF-8</literal>\" is good idea if you use non-English environment."
msgstr "En dposant un signalement de bogue, c'est une bonne ide de lancer et de vrifier la commande &nbsp;<literal>LANG=en_US.UTF-8</literal>&nbsp; si vous utilisez un environnement autre que l'environnement anglais."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:3874
msgid "See <literal>locale</literal>(5) and <literal>locale</literal>(7) for \"<literal>$LANG</literal>\" and related environment variables."
msgstr "Voir <literal>locale</literal>(5) et <literal>locale</literal>(7) pour les variables d'environnement &nbsp;<literal>$LANG</literal>&nbsp; et associes."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:3876
msgid "I recommend you to configure the system environment just by the \"<literal>$LANG</literal>\" variable and to stay away from \"<literal>$LC_*</literal>\" variables unless it is absolutely needed."
msgstr "Je vous recommande de configurer l'environnement du systme en ne touchant qu' la variable &nbsp;<literal>$LANG</literal>&nbsp; en laissant de ct les variables &nbsp;<literal>$LC_*</literal>&nbsp;  moins que ce ne soit absolument ncessaire."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><title>
