msgid "If a desktop GUI program experienced instability after significant upstream version upgrade, you should suspect interferences with old local configuration files created by it. If it is stable under newly created user account, this hypothesis is confirmed.  (This is a bug of packaging and usually avoided by the packager.)"
msgstr "Si un programme avec une interface graphique prsente une instabilit aprs une mise  niveau amont importante, vous devriez songer  des interfrences avec les anciens fichiers de configurations locaux qu'il avait cr. S'il est stable avec un compte d'utilisateur frachement cr, cette hypothse est confirme. (C'est un bogue de ralisation du paquet et c'est le plus souvent vit par le responsable du paquet)."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8141
msgid "To recover stability, you should move corresponding local configuration files and restart the GUI program.  You may need to read old configuration file contents to recover configuration information later.  (Do not erase them too quickly.)"
msgstr "Pour retrouver la stabilit, vous devrez dplacer les fichiers de configuration locaux et redmarrer le programme ayant une interface graphique. Il vous faudra peut-tre lire le contenu de l'ancien fichier de configuration pour retrouver plus tard vos informations de configuration. (Ne les effacez pas trop rapidement)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8144
msgid "Different packages with overlapped files"
msgstr "Diffrents paquets ayant des fichiers communs"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8145
msgid "Archive level package management systems, such as <literal>aptitude</literal>(8) or <literal>apt-get</literal>(1), do not even try to install packages with overlapped files using package dependencies (see <xref linkend=\"_package_dependencies\"/>)."
msgstr "Les systme de gestion d'archive au niveau du paquet, tels qu'<literal>aptitude</literal>(8) ou <literal>apt-get</literal>(1) ne tenteront mme pas, grce aux dpendances des paquets, d'installer des paquet ayant des fichiers qui se superposent (voir <xref linkend=\"_package_dependencies\"/>)."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8146
msgid "Errors by the package maintainer or deployment of inconsistently mixed source of archives (see <xref linkend=\"_packages_from_mixed_source_of_archives\"/>) by the system administrator may create situation with incorrectly defined package dependencies. When you install a package with overlapped files using <literal>aptitude</literal>(8) or <literal>apt-get</literal>(1) under such situation, <literal>dpkg</literal>(1) which unpacks package ensures to return error to the calling program without overwriting existing files."
msgstr "Des erreurs du responsable du paquet ou le dploiement de sources d'archives mlanges et incohrentes (voir <xref linkend=\"_packages_from_mixed_source_of_archives\"/>) par l'administrateur du systme peuvent crer une situation o les dpendances des paquets sont dcrites de manire incorrecte. Lorsque, dans une telle situation, vous installez un paquet qui crase des fichiers en utilisant <literal>aptitude</literal>(8) ou <literal>apt-get</literal>(1), <literal>dpkg</literal>(1) qui dpaquette le paquet va retourner une erreur au programme appelant sans craser les fichiers existants."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8148
msgid "The use of third party packages introduces significant system risks via maintainer scripts which are run with root privilege and can do anything to your system.  The <literal>dpkg</literal>(1) command only protects against overwriting by the unpacking."
msgstr "Lutilisation de programmes tierce partie introduit un risque significatif par l'intermdiaire des scripts du responsable qui sont lancs avec les privilges de l'administrateur et peuvent effectuer n'importe quoi sur votre systme. La commande <literal>dpkg</literal>(1) ne protge que contre l'crasement des fichiers lors du dpaquetage."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8150
msgid "You can work around such broken installation by removing the old offending package, <literal>&lt;old-package&gt;</literal>, first."
msgstr "Vous pouvez contourner un tel problme d'installation casse en supprimant d'abord l'ancien paquet, <literal>&lt;ancien_paquet&gt;</literal>, qui pose des problmes."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8151
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ sudo dpkg -P &lt;old-package&gt;"
msgstr "$ sudo dpkg -P &lt;ancien_paquet&gt;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8154
msgid "Fixing broken package script"
msgstr "Corriger les scripts casss des paquets"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8155
msgid "When a command in the package script returns error for some reason and the script exits with error, the package management system aborts their action and ends up with partially installed packages.  When a package contains bugs in its removal scripts, the package may become impossible to remove and quite nasty."
msgstr "Lorsqu'une commande dans le script du paquet retourne une erreur pour une raison quelconque et que le script retourne une erreur, le systme de gestion des paquets arrte son action et se termine en laissant des paquets partiellement installs. Lorsqu'un paquet comporte des bogues dans les scripts de suppression, le paquet peut devenir impossible  supprimer et assez dplaisant."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8156
msgid "For the package script problem of \"<literal>&lt;package_name&gt;</literal>\", you should look into following package scripts."
msgstr "Pour les problmes avec le script de paquet de &nbsp;<literal>&lt;nom_paquet&gt;</literal>&nbsp;, il vous faudra regarder dans les scripts des paquets&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8160
msgid "\"<literal>/var/lib/dpkg/info/&lt;package_name&gt;.preinst</literal>\""
msgstr "&nbsp;<literal>/var/lib/dpkg/info/&lt;nom_paquet&gt;.preinst</literal>&nbsp;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8165
msgid "\"<literal>/var/lib/dpkg/info/&lt;package_name&gt;.postinst</literal>\""
msgstr "&nbsp;<literal>/var/lib/dpkg/info/&lt;nom_paquet&gt;.postinst</literal>&nbsp;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8170
msgid "\"<literal>/var/lib/dpkg/info/&lt;package_name&gt;.prerm</literal>\""
msgstr "&nbsp;<literal>/var/lib/dpkg/info/&lt;nom_paquet&gt;.prerm</literal>&nbsp;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8175
msgid "\"<literal>/var/lib/dpkg/info/&lt;package_name&gt;.postrm</literal>\""
msgstr "&nbsp;<literal>/var/lib/dpkg/info/&lt;nom_paquet&gt;.postrm</literal>&nbsp;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8179
msgid "Edit the offending package script from the root using following techniques."
msgstr "ditez le script du paquet posant problme avec le compte de l'administrateur en utilisant les technique suivantes&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8183
msgid "disable the offending line by preceding \"<literal>#</literal>\""
msgstr "dsactiver la ligne posant problme avec un &nbsp;<literal>#</literal> en tte de ligne&nbsp;;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8188
msgid "force to return success by appending the offending line with \"<literal>|| true</literal>\""
msgstr "forcer un retour avec succs en ajoutant  la fin de l ligne qui pose problme &nbsp;<literal>|| true</literal>&nbsp;."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8192
msgid "Configure all partially installed packages with the following command."
msgstr "Configurez tous les paquets partiellement installs  l'aide de la commande suivante&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8193
#, no-wrap
msgid "# dpkg --configure -a"
msgstr "# dpkg --configure -a"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8196
msgid "Rescue with the dpkg command"
msgstr "Rcupration avec la commande dpkg"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8197
msgid "Since <literal>dpkg</literal> is very low level package tool, it can function under the very bad situation such as unbootable system without network connection.  Let's assume <literal>foo</literal> package was broken and needs to be replaced."
msgstr "Comme <literal>dpkg</literal> est un outils de gestion des paquets de trs bas niveau, il peut fonctionner dans des situations trs difficiles telles qu'un systme qu'on ne peut pas dmarrer et qui n'a pas de connexion rseau. Supposons que le paquet <literal>toto</literal> soit cass et doive tre remplac."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8198
msgid "You may still find cached copies of older bug free version of <literal>foo</literal> package in the package cache directory: \"<literal>/var/cache/apt/archives/</literal>\".  (If not, you can download it from archive of <ulink url=\"&httpsnapshotdebiannet;\">http://snapshot.debian.net/</ulink> or copy it from package cache of a functioning machine.)"
msgstr "Vous pouvez trouver des copies de l'ancienne version du paquet <literal>foo</literal> sans bogue dans le rpertoire de cache des paquets &nbsp;<literal>/var/cache/apt/archives/</literal>&nbsp;. (Si ce n'est pas le cas, vous pouvez tlcharger l'archive depuis <ulink url=\"&httpsnapshotdebiannet;\">http://snapshot.debian.net/</ulink> ou la copier depuis le cache des paquets d'une machine qui fonctionne)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8199
msgid "If you can boot the system, you may install it by the following command."
msgstr "Si vous pouvez dmarrer le systme, vous pouvez l'installer avec la commande suivante&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8200
#, no-wrap
msgid "# dpkg -i /path/to/foo_&lt;old_version&gt;_&lt;arch&gt;.deb"
msgstr "# dpkg -i /chemin/vers/toto_&lt;ancienne-version&gt;_&lt;arch&gt;.deb"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8202
msgid "If system breakage is minor, you may alternatively downgrade the whole system as <xref linkend=\"_emergency_downgrading\"/> using the higher level APT system."
msgstr "Si la casse du systme est minime, vous pouvez faire un retour en arrire (downgrade) de tout le systme comme <xref linkend=\"_emergency_downgrading\"/> en utilisant le systme de plus haut niveau APT."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8204
msgid "If your system is unbootable from hard disk, you should seek other ways to boot it."
msgstr "Si votre systme ne peut pas tre dmarr depuis le disque dur, vous devrez rechercher d'autres manires de le dmarrer&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8208
msgid "Boot the system using the debian-installer CD in rescue mode."
msgstr "Dmarrez le systme en utilisant le CD de l'installateur Debian en mode secours (&nbsp;rescue mode&nbsp;)."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8213
msgid "Mount the unbootable system on the hard disk to \"<literal>/target</literal>\"."
msgstr "Montez le systme qui ne veut pas dmarrer sur le disque dur sur &nbsp;<literal>/target</literal>&nbsp;."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8218
msgid "Install older version of <literal>foo</literal> package by the following."
msgstr "Installez une version plus ancienne du paquet <literal>toto</literal> en faisant de qui suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8222
#, no-wrap
msgid "# dpkg --root /target -i /path/to/foo_&lt;old_version&gt;_&lt;arch&gt;.deb"
msgstr "# dpkg --root /target -i /chemin/vers/toto_&lt;ancienne_version&gt;_&lt;arch&gt;.deb"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8223
msgid "This example works even if the <literal>dpkg</literal> command on the hard disk is broken."
msgstr "Cet exemple fonctionne mme si la commande <literal>dpkg</literal> qui se trouve sur le disque dur est casse."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8225
msgid "Any GNU/Linux system started by another system on hard disk, live GNU/Linux CD, bootable USB-key drive, or netboot can be used similarly to rescue broken system."
msgstr "Tous les systmes GNU/Linux dmarrs depuis un autre systme sur le disque dur, depuis un CD autonome GNU/Linux, depuis une cl USB amorable, depuis le rseau peuvent tre utiliss de manire similaire pour restaurer un systme cass."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8227
msgid "If attempting to install a package this way fails due to some dependency violations and you really need to do this as the last resort, you can override dependency using <literal>dpkg</literal>'s \"<literal>--ignore-depends</literal>\", \"<literal>--force-depends</literal>\" and other options.  If you do this, you need to make serious effort to restore proper dependency later. See <literal>dpkg</literal>(8) for details."
msgstr "Si la tentative d'installation d'un paquet de cette manire choue en raison de la violation de certaines dpendances et que vous voulez vraiment le faire, vous pouvez, en dernier ressort, outrepasser les dpendances en utilisant les options &nbsp;<literal>--ignore-depends</literal>&nbsp;, &nbsp;<literal>--force-depends</literal>&nbsp; de <literal>dpkg</literal>et d'autres options. Si vous le faites, vous aurez un srieux effort  faire pour restaurer les dpendances correctes par la suite. Voir <literal>dpkg</literal>(8) pour davantage d'informations."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8229
msgid "When your system is seriously broken, you should make a full backup of system to a safe place (see <xref linkend=\"_backup_and_recovery\"/>) and should perform a clean installation.  This is less time consuming and produces better results in the end."
msgstr "Lorsque votre systme est srieusement cass, vous devriez faire une sauvegarde complte du systme dans un endroit sr (voir <xref linkend=\"_backup_and_recovery\"/>) et effectuer une installation propre. Cela demande moins de temps et donne, en fin de compte, de meilleurs rsultats."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8233
msgid "Recovering package selection data"
msgstr "Rcuprer les donnes de slection des paquets"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8234
msgid "If \"<literal>/var/lib/dpkg/status</literal>\" becomes corrupt for any reason, the Debian system loses package selection data and suffers severely.  Look for the old \"<literal>/var/lib/dpkg/status</literal>\" file at \"<literal>/var/lib/dpkg/status-old</literal>\" or \"<literal>/var/backups/dpkg.status.*</literal>\"."
msgstr "Si le fichier &nbsp;<literal>/var/lib/dpkg/status</literal>&nbsp; est corrompu pour une raison quelconque, le systme Debian perd les donnes de paquets slectionns et est srieusement endommag. Regardez l'ancienne version du fichier &nbsp;<literal>/var/lib/dpkg/status</literal>&nbsp; dans &nbsp;<literal>/var/lib/dpkg/status-old</literal>&nbsp; ou &nbsp;<literal>/var/backups/dpkg.status.*</literal>&nbsp;."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8235
msgid "Keeping \"<literal>/var/backups/</literal>\" in a separate partition may be a good idea since this directory contains lots of important system data."
msgstr "Conserver &nbsp;<literal>/var/backups/</literal>&nbsp; sur une partition spare peut tre une bonne ide car ce rpertoire contient de nombreuses donnes importantes du systme."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8236
msgid "For serious breakage, I recommend to make fresh re-install after making backup of the system. Even if everything in \"<literal>/var/</literal>\" is gone, you can still recover some information from directories in \"<literal>/usr/share/doc/</literal>\" to guide your new installation."
msgstr "Pour les casses svres, je recommande de faire une rinstallation propre aprs avoir fait une sauvegarde du systme. Mme si vous avez perdu tout ce qui se trouve dans &nbsp;<literal>/var/</literal>&nbsp;, vous pouvez encore rcuprer certaines informations depuis les rpertoires qui se trouvent dans &nbsp;<literal>/usr/share/doc/</literal>&nbsp; afin de vous guider dans votre nouvelle installation."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8237
msgid "Reinstall minimal (desktop) system."
msgstr "Rinstaller un systme (de bureau) minimum."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8238
#, no-wrap
msgid "# mkdir -p /path/to/old/system"
msgstr "# mkdir -p /chemin/vers/ancien/systme"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8239
msgid "Mount old system at \"<literal>/path/to/old/system/</literal>\"."
msgstr "Montez l'ancien systme sur &nbsp;<literal>/chemin/vers/ancien/systme/</literal>&nbsp;."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8240
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# cd /path/to/old/system/usr/share/doc\n"
"# ls -1 &gt;~/ls1.txt\n"
"# cd /usr/share/doc\n"
"# ls -1 &gt;&gt;~/ls1.txt\n"
"# cd\n"
"# sort ls1.txt | uniq | less"
msgstr ""
"# cd /chemin/vers/ancien/systme/usr/share/doc\n"
"# ls -1 &gt;~/ls1.txt\n"
"# cd /usr/share/doc\n"
"# ls -1 &gt;&gt;~/ls1.txt\n"
"# cd\n"
"# sort ls1.txt | uniq | less"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8246
msgid "Then you are presented with package names to install.  (There may be some non-package names such as \"<literal>texmf</literal>\".)"
msgstr "Le systme vous prsentera alors les noms de paquets  installer. (Il peut y avoir des noms qui ne soient pas des noms de paquets, comme, par exemple, &nbsp;<literal>texmf</literal>&nbsp;)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8250
msgid "Tips for the package management"
msgstr "Astuces pour la gestion des paquets"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8252
msgid "How to pick Debian packages"
msgstr "Comment obtenir des paquets Debian"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8253
msgid "You can seek packages which satisfy your needs with <literal>aptitude</literal> from the package description or from the list under \"Tasks\"."
msgstr "Vous pouvez rechercher les paquets qui satisfont  vos besoins avec <literal>aptitude</literal>  partir de la description du paquet ou depuis la liste se trouvant dans &nbsp;Tasks&nbsp;."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8254
msgid "When you encounter more than 2 similar packages and wonder which one to install without \"trial and error\" efforts, you should use some <emphasis role=\"strong\">common sense</emphasis>.  I consider following points are good indications of preferred packages."
msgstr "Si vous trouvez deux paquets similaires et que vous vous demandez lequel installer sans faire des efforts d'&nbsp;essais et erreurs&nbsp;, vous pouvez user de <emphasis role=\"strong\">bon sens</emphasis>. Je considre que les points suivants constituent de bonnes indications pour les paquets  privilgier&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8258
msgid "Essential: yes &gt; no"
msgstr "Essential&nbsp;: yes &gt; no"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8263
msgid "Component: main &gt; contrib &gt; non-free"
msgstr "Composante&nbsp;: main &gt; contrib &gt; non-free"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8268
msgid "Priority: required &gt; important &gt; standard &gt; optional &gt; extra"
msgstr "Priorit&nbsp;: required &gt; important &gt; standard &gt; optional &gt; extra"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8273
msgid "Tasks: packages listed in tasks such as \"Desktop environment\""
msgstr "Tches&nbsp;: paquets affichs dans les tches tels que &nbsp;Environnement de bureau&nbsp;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8278
msgid "Packages selected by the dependency package (e.g., <literal>python2.4</literal> by <literal>python</literal>)"
msgstr "Les paquets slectionns par le paquet de dpendances (par exemple, <literal>python2.4</literal> par <literal>python</literal>)"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8283
msgid "Popcon: higher in the vote and install number"
msgstr "Popcon&nbsp;: les votes et le nombre d'installations les plus levs"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8288
msgid "Changelog: regular updates by the maintainer"
msgstr "Journaux des modifications (&nbsp;Changelog&nbsp;&nbsp;: mises  jour rgulires par le responsable"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8293
msgid "BTS: No RC bugs (no critical, no grave, and no serious bugs)"
msgstr "BTS&nbsp;: pas de bogue RC (pas de bogue critique, grave ou srieux)"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8298
msgid "BTS: responsive maintainer to bug reports"
msgstr "BTS&nbsp;: ractivit du responsable aux signalements de bogues"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8303
msgid "BTS: higher number of the recently fixed bugs"
msgstr "BTS&nbsp;: le plus grand nombre de bogues rgls rcemment"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8308
msgid "BTS: lower number of remaining non-wishlist bugs"
msgstr "BTS&nbsp;: le plus faible nombre de bogues restants qui ne soient pas dans la liste des vux"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8312
msgid "Debian being a volunteer project with distributed development model, its archive contains many packages with different focus and quality.  You must make your own decision what to do with them."
msgstr "Debian tant un modle de projet volontaire avec un dveloppement distribu, son archive contient de nombreux paquets avec des cibles diffrentes et de qualit variable. Vous devrez choisir vous-mme ce que vous voulez en faire."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8315
msgid "Packages from mixed source of archives"
msgstr "Paquets venant de sources mlanges"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8317
