msgstr "La valeur de Pin-Priority associe uniquement avec &lt;paquet&gt; est affiche sur la partie droite de toutes les chanes de version, par exemple, &nbsp;<literal>0.181 700</literal>&nbsp;."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8518
msgid "\"<literal>0</literal>\" is listed right side of all version strings if no association just with &lt;package&gt; is defined, e.g., \"<literal>0.181 0</literal>\"."
msgstr "&nbsp;<literal>0</literal>&nbsp; est affich  droite de toutes les chanes de version s'il n'y a pas d'association dfinie avec uniquement &lt;package&gt;, par exemple, &nbsp;<literal>0.181 0</literal>&nbsp;."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8523
msgid "The Pin-Priority values of archives (defined as \"<literal>Package: *</literal>\" in the \"<literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal>\" file) are listed left side of all archive paths, e.g., \"<literal>200 http://backports.org etch-backports/main Packages</literal>\"."
msgstr "Les valeurs de Pin-Priority des archives (dfinies par &nbsp;<literal>Package: *</literal>&nbsp; dans le fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal>&nbsp;) sont affiches sur la gauche de tous les chemins vers les archives, par exemple, &nbsp;<literal>200 http://backports.org etch-backports/main Packages</literal>&nbsp;."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8527
msgid "Here is an example of <emphasis role=\"strong\">apt-pinning</emphasis> technique to include specific newer upstream version packages found in <literal>unstable</literal> regularly upgraded while tracking <literal>testing</literal>.  You list all required archives in the \"<literal>/etc/apt/sources.list</literal>\" file as the following."
msgstr "Voici un exemple de technique d'<emphasis role=\"strong\">pinglage apt </emphasis> permettant d'inclure de manire rgulire une version amont plus rcente de paquets spcifiques se trouvant dans <literal>unstable</literal> tout en suivant <literal>testing</literal>. Listez toutes les archives ncessaires dans le fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/sources.list</literal>&nbsp; de la manire suivante&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8528
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"deb http://ftp.us.debian.org/debian/ testing main contrib non-free\n"
"deb http://ftp.us.debian.org/debian/ unstable main contrib non-free\n"
"deb http://security.debian.org/ testing/updates main contrib"
msgstr ""
"deb http://ftp.fr.debian.org/debian/ testing main contrib non-free\n"
"deb http://ftp.fr.debian.org/debian/ unstable main contrib non-free\n"
"deb http://security.debian.org/ testing/updates main contrib"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8531
msgid "Set the \"<literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal>\" file as as the following."
msgstr "Configurez le fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal>&nbsp; comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8532
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Package: *\n"
"Pin: release a=testing\n"
"Pin-Priority: 500\n"
"\n"
"Package: *\n"
"Pin: release a=unstable\n"
"Pin-Priority: 200"
msgstr ""
"Package: *\n"
"Pin: release a=testing\n"
"Pin-Priority: 500\n"
"\n"
"Package: *\n"
"Pin: release a=unstable\n"
"Pin-Priority: 200"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8539
msgid "When you wish to install a package named \"<literal>&lt;package-name&gt;</literal>\" with its dependencies from <literal>unstable</literal> archive under this configuration, you issue the following command which switches target release with \"<literal>-t</literal>\" option (Pin-Priority of <literal>unstable</literal> becomes 990.)."
msgstr "Lorsque vous dsirez installer un paquet appel &nbsp;<literal>&lt;nom_paquet&gt;</literal>&nbsp; avec ses dpendances depuis l'archive <literal>unstable</literal> avec cette configuration, vous utilisez la commande suivante qui modifie la version cible avec l'option &nbsp;<literal>-t</literal>&nbsp; (la priorit d'pinglage de <literal>unstable</literal> devient 990.)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8540
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ sudo apt-get install -t unstable &lt;package-name&gt;"
msgstr "$ sudo apt-get install -t unstable &lt;nom_paquet&gt;"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8541
msgid "With this configuration, usual execution of \"<literal>apt-get upgrade</literal>\" and \"<literal>apt-get dist-upgrade</literal>\" (or \"<literal>aptitude safe-upgrade</literal>\" and \"<literal>aptitude full-upgrade</literal>\" for <literal>squeeze</literal>) upgrades packages which were installed from <literal>testing</literal> archive using current <literal>testing</literal> archive and packages which were installed from <literal>unstable</literal> archive using current <literal>unstable</literal> archive."
msgstr "Avec cette configuration, l'excution habituelle de &nbsp;<literal>apt-get upgrade</literal>&nbsp; et &nbsp;<literal>apt-get dist-upgrade</literal>&nbsp; (ou &nbsp;<literal>aptitude safe-upgrade</literal>&nbsp; et &nbsp;<literal>aptitude full-upgrade</literal>&nbsp; pour <literal>squeeze</literal>) met  niveau les paquets qui avaient t installs depuis l'archive <literal>testing</literal> en utilisant l'archive <literal>testing</literal> actuelle et les paquets qui avaient t installs depuis l'archive <literal>unstable</literal> en utilisant l'archive <literal>unstable</literal> actuelle."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8543
msgid "Be careful not to remove \"<literal>testing</literal>\" entry from the \"<literal>/etc/apt/sources.list</literal>\" file.  Without \"<literal>testing</literal>\" entry in it, APT system upgrades packages using newer <literal>unstable</literal> archive."
msgstr "Faites bien attention  ne pas supprimer l'entre &nbsp;<literal>testing</literal>&nbsp; du fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/sources.list</literal>&nbsp;.  Sans l'entre &nbsp;<literal>testing</literal>&nbsp;, le systme APT mettra  niveau les paquets en utilisant la nouvelle archive <literal>unstable</literal>."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8546
msgid "I usually edit the \"<literal>/etc/apt/sources.list</literal>\" file to comment out \"<literal>unstable</literal>\" archive entry right after above operation.  This avoids slow update process of having too many entries in the \"<literal>/etc/apt/sources.list</literal>\" file although this prevents upgrading packages which were installed from <literal>unstable</literal> archive using current <literal>unstable</literal> archive."
msgstr "J'dite habituellement le fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/sources.list</literal>&nbsp; en commentant l'entre correspondant  l'archive &nbsp;<literal>unstable</literal>&nbsp; juste aprs avoir effectu les oprations ci-dessus. Ceci vite un processus de mise  jour lent en raison du nombre trop important d'entres dans le fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/sources.list</literal>&nbsp; bien que ceci ne permette pas de mettre  niveau les paquets qui avaient t installs depuis l'archive <literal>unstable</literal> en utilisant l'archive <literal>unstable</literal> actuelle."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8549
msgid "If \"<literal>Pin-Priority: 20</literal>\" is used instead of \"<literal>Pin-Priority: 200</literal>\" for the \"<literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal>\" file, already installed packages having Pin-Priority value of 100 are not upgraded by <literal>unstable</literal> archive even if \"<literal>testing</literal>\" entry in the \"<literal>/etc/apt/sources.list</literal>\" file is removed."
msgstr "Si on utilise &nbsp;<literal>Pin-Priority: 20</literal>&nbsp;  la place de <literal>Pin-Priority: 200</literal>&nbsp; pour le fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal>&nbsp;, les paquets dj installs ayant une valeur de Pin-Priority de 100 ne seront pas mis  niveau depuis l'archive <literal>unstable</literal> mme si l'entre &nbsp;<literal>testing</literal>&nbsp; du fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/sources.list</literal>&nbsp; est supprime."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8551
msgid "If you wish to track particular packages in <literal>unstable</literal> automatically without initial \"<literal>-t unstable</literal>\" installation, you must create the \"<literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal>\" file and explicitly list all those packages at the top of it as the following."
msgstr "Si vous dsirez suivre automatiquement un paquet particulier dans <literal>unstable</literal> sans une installation initiale &nbsp;<literal>-t unstable</literal>&nbsp;, vous devrez crer le fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal>&nbsp; et lister explicitement en dbut de ce fichier tous ces paquets de la manire suivante&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8552
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Package: &lt;package-1&gt;\n"
"Pin: release a=unstable\n"
"Pin-Priority: 700\n"
"\n"
"Package: &lt;package-2&gt;\n"
"Pin: release a=unstable\n"
"Pin-Priority: 700"
msgstr ""
"Package: &lt;paquet-1&gt;\n"
"Pin: release a=unstable\n"
"Pin-Priority: 700\n"
"\n"
"Package: &lt;paquet-2&gt;\n"
"Pin: release a=unstable\n"
"Pin-Priority: 700"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8559
msgid "These set Pin-Priority value for each specific package.  For example, in order to track the latest <literal>unstable</literal> version of this \"Debian Reference\" in English, you should have following entries in the \"<literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal>\" file."
msgstr "Ceci dfinit la valeur de Pin-Priority pour chacun de ces paquets spcifiques. Par exemple, pour suivre la dernire version <literal>unstable</literal> de cette &nbsp;Rfrence Debian&nbsp; en franais, vous devrez ajouter les entres suivantes dans le fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal>&nbsp;."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8560
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Package: debian-reference-en\n"
"Pin: release a=unstable\n"
"Pin-Priority: 700\n"
"\n"
"Package: debian-reference-common\n"
"Pin: release a=unstable\n"
"Pin-Priority: 700"
msgstr ""
"Package: debian-reference-fr\n"
"Pin: release a=unstable\n"
"Pin-Priority: 700\n"
"\n"
"Package: debian-reference-common\n"
"Pin: release a=unstable\n"
"Pin-Priority: 700"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8568
msgid "This apt-pinning technique is valid even when you are tracking <literal>stable</literal> archive.  Documentation packages have been always safe to install from <literal>unstable</literal> archive in my experience, so far."
msgstr "Cette technique d'pinglage apt est aussi valable si vous suivez l'archive <literal>stable</literal>.  Jusqu' prsent et selon mon exprience, les paquets de documentation ont toujours t srs  installer depuis l'archive <literal>unstable</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8570
msgid "Here is another example of <emphasis role=\"strong\">apt-pinning</emphasis> technique to include specific newer upstream version packages found in <literal>experimental</literal> while tracking <literal>unstable</literal>.  You list all required archives in the \"<literal>/etc/apt/sources.list</literal>\" file as the following."
msgstr "Voici un autre exemple de technique d'<emphasis role=\"strong\">pinglage apt</emphasis> destine  inclure une version amont plus rcente de paquets spcifiques se trouvant dans <literal>experimental</literal> tout en suivant <literal>unstable</literal>.  Vous listez toutes les archives ncessaires dans fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/sources.list</literal>&nbsp; de la manire suivante&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8571
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"deb http://ftp.us.debian.org/debian/ unstable main contrib non-free\n"
"deb http://ftp.us.debian.org/debian/ experimental main contrib non-free\n"
"deb http://security.debian.org/ testing/updates main contrib"
msgstr ""
"deb http://ftp.us.debian.org/debian/ unstable main contrib non-free\n"
"deb http://ftp.us.debian.org/debian/ experimental main contrib non-free\n"
"deb http://security.debian.org/ testing/updates main contrib"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8574
msgid "The default Pin-Priority value for <literal>experimental</literal> archive is always 1 (&lt;&lt;100) since it is <emphasis role=\"strong\">NotAutomatic</emphasis> archive (see <xref linkend=\"_archive_level_release_files\"/>).  There is no need to set Pin-Priority value explicitly in the \"<literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal>\" file just to use <literal>experimental</literal> archive unless you wish to track particular packages in it automatically for next upgrading."
msgstr "La valeur de Pin-Priority par dfaut pour l'archive <literal>experimental</literal> est toujours de 1 (&lt;&lt;100) car c'est une archive <emphasis role=\"strong\">NotAutomatic</emphasis> (voir <xref linkend=\"_archive_level_release_files\"/>). Il n'y a pas besoin de dfinir explicitement de valeur de Pin-Priority  dans le fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal>&nbsp; simplement pour utiliser l'archive <literal>experimental</literal>  moins que vous ne dsiriez suivre des paquets particulier dans cette archive de manire automatique pour la mise  niveau suivante."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8577
msgid "Volatile and Backports.org"
msgstr "Volatile et Backports.org"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8578
msgid "There are <ulink url=\"&debianvolatileproject;\">debian-volatile project</ulink> and <ulink url=\"&backportsorg;\">backports.org</ulink> archives which provide updgrade packages for <literal>stable</literal>."
msgstr "Les archives du <ulink url=\"&debianvolatileproject;\">projet debian-volatile</ulink> et <ulink url=\"&backportsorg;\">backports.org</ulink> fournissent des paquets mis  niveau pour <literal>stable</literal>."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><warning><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><warning><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8580
msgid "Do not use all packages available in the <emphasis role=\"strong\">NotAutomatic</emphasis> archives such as <literal>&codename-stable;-backports</literal> and <literal>volatile-sloppy</literal>.  Use only selected packages which fits your needs."
msgstr "N'utilisez pas tous les paquets disponibles dans des archives <emphasis role=\"strong\">NotAutomatic</emphasis> telles que <literal>&codename-stable;-backports</literal> et <literal>volatile-sloppy</literal>.  N'utilisez que des paquets slectionns qui rpondent  vos besoins."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8583
msgid "<ulink url=\"&backportsorg;\">backports.org</ulink> is a non-Debian archive, although its packages are signed by Debian developers."
msgstr "<ulink url=\"&backportsorg;\">backports.org</ulink> est une archive non Debian, cependant ses paquets sont signs par des dveloppeurs de Debian."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8586
msgid "Archive level Release files (see <xref linkend=\"_archive_level_release_files\"/>) are used for the rule of <literal>apt_preferences</literal>(5).  Thus apt-pinning works only with \"code\" name for <ulink url=\"&volatiledebianarchives;\">volatile Debian archives</ulink>. This is different from other Debian archives.  For example, you can do \"<literal>Pin: release a=&codename-stable;</literal>\" but can not do \"<literal>Pin: release a=stable</literal>\" in the \"<literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal>\" file for volatile Debian archives."
msgstr "Les fichiers Release du niveau de l'archive (voir <xref linkend=\"_archive_level_release_files\"/>) sont utiliss pour la rgle de <literal>apt_preferences</literal>(5).  L'pinglage apt ne fonctionne donc que pour les noms de &nbsp;code&nbsp; pour les <ulink url=\"&volatiledebianarchives;\">archive Debian volatile </ulink>. Ceci est diffrent des autres archives Debian. Par exemple, vous pouvez mettre &nbsp;<literal>Pin: release a=&codename-stable;</literal>&nbsp; mais ne pouvez pas mettre &nbsp;<literal>Pin: release a=stable</literal>&nbsp; dans le fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal>&nbsp; pour les archives Debian volatile."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8588
msgid "Here is an example of <emphasis role=\"strong\">apt-pinning</emphasis> technique to include specific newer upstream version packages found in <literal>&codename-stable;-backports</literal> while tracking <literal>&codename-stable;</literal> and <literal>volatile</literal>.  You list all required archives in the \"<literal>/etc/apt/sources.list</literal>\" file as the following."
msgstr "Voici un exemple de technique d'<emphasis role=\"strong\">pinglage apt</emphasis> pour inclure une version amont plus rcente de paquets spcifiques se trouvant dans <literal>&codename-stable;-backports</literal> tout en suivant <literal>&codename-stable;</literal> et <literal>volatile</literal>. Vous listez tous les archives ncessaires dans le fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/sources.list</literal>&nbsp; comme suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8589
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"deb http://ftp.us.debian.org/debian/ &codename-stable; main contrib non-free\n"
"deb http://security.debian.org/ &codename-stable;/updates main contrib\n"
"deb http://volatile.debian.org/debian-volatile/ &codename-stable;/volatile main contrib non-free\n"
"deb http://volatile.debian.org/debian-volatile/ &codename-stable;/volatile-sloppy main contrib non-free\n"
"deb http://backports.org/debian/ &codename-stable;-backports main contrib non-free"
msgstr ""
"deb http://ftp.us.debian.org/debian/ &codename-stable; main contrib non-free\n"
"deb http://security.debian.org/ &codename-stable;/updates main contrib\n"
"deb http://volatile.debian.org/debian-volatile/ &codename-stable;/volatile main contrib non-free\n"
"deb http://volatile.debian.org/debian-volatile/ &codename-stable;/volatile-sloppy main contrib non-free\n"
"deb http://backports.org/debian/ &codename-stable;-backports main contrib non-free"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8594
msgid "The default Pin-Priority value for <ulink url=\"&backportsorg;\">backports.org</ulink> and <literal>volatile-sloppy</literal> archives are always 1 (&lt;&lt;100) since they are <emphasis role=\"strong\">NotAutomatic</emphasis> archive (see <xref linkend=\"_archive_level_release_files\"/>).  There is no need to set Pin-Priority value explicitly in the \"<literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal>\" file just to use for <ulink url=\"&backportsorg;\">backports.org</ulink> and <literal>volatile-sloppy</literal> archive unless you wish to track packages automatically for next upgrading."
msgstr "La valeur par dfaut de Pin-Priority pour les archives <ulink url=\"&backportsorg;\">backports.org</ulink> et <literal>volatile-sloppy</literal> est toujours de 1 (&lt;&lt;100) car ce sont des archives <emphasis role=\"strong\">non automatiques</emphasis> (voir <xref linkend=\"_archive_level_release_files\"/>). Il n'y a pas besoin de dfinir explicitement la valeur de Pin-Priority dans le fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal>&nbsp; uniquement pour pouvoir utiliser les archives <ulink url=\"&backportsorg;\">backports.org</ulink> et <literal>volatile-sloppy</literal>  moins que vous ne dsiriez suivre automatiquement des paquets pour la mise  niveau suivante."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8595
msgid "So whenever you wish to install a package named \"<literal>&lt;package-name&gt;</literal>\" with its dependency from <literal>&codename-stable;-backports</literal> archive, you use following command while switching target release with \"<literal>-t</literal>\" option."
msgstr "Donc, chaque fois que vous dsirerez installer un paquet nomm &nbsp;<literal>&lt;nom_paquet&gt;</literal>&nbsp; avec ses dpendances  depuis l'archive <literal>&codename-stable;-backports</literal>, vous utiliserez la commande suivante en changeant de version cible avec l'option &nbsp;<literal>-t</literal>&nbsp;&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8596
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ sudo apt-get install -t &codename-stable;-backports &lt;package-name&gt;"
msgstr "$ sudo apt-get install -t &codename-stable;-backports &lt;package-nom_paquet&gt;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8597
msgid "If you wish to upgrade particular packages, you must create the \"<literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal>\" file and explicitly lists all packages in it as the following."
msgstr "Si vous dsirez mettre  niveau des paquets particuliers, vous devez crer le fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal>&nbsp; et y lister explicitement tous les paquets comme suit&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8598
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Package: &lt;package-1&gt;\n"
"Pin: release o=Backports.org archive\n"
"Pin-Priority: 700\n"
"\n"
"Package: &lt;package-2&gt;\n"
"Pin: release o=volatile.debian.org\n"
"Pin-Priority: 700"
msgstr ""
"Package: &lt;paquet-1&gt;\n"
"Pin: release o=Backports.org archive\n"
"Pin-Priority: 700\n"
"\n"
"Package: &lt;paquet-2&gt;\n"
"Pin: release o=volatile.debian.org\n"
"Pin-Priority: 700"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8605
msgid "Alternatively, with the \"<literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal>\" file as the following."
msgstr "Vous pouvez aussi configurer le fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal>&nbsp; de la manire suivante&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8606
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Package: *\n"
"Pin: release a=stable , o=Debian\n"
"Pin-Priority: 500\n"
"\n"
"Package: *\n"
"Pin: release a=&codename-stable;, o=volatile.debian.org\n"
"Pin-Priority: 500\n"
"\n"
"Package: *\n"
"Pin: release a=&codename-stable;-backports, o=Backports.org archive\n"
"Pin-Priority: 200\n"
"\n"
"Package: *\n"
"Pin: release a=&codename-stable;-sloppy, o=volatile.debian.org\n"
"Pin-Priority: 200"
msgstr ""
"Package: *\n"
"Pin: release a=stable , o=Debian\n"
"Pin-Priority: 500\n"
"\n"
"Package: *\n"
"Pin: release a=&codename-stable;, o=volatile.debian.org\n"
"Pin-Priority: 500\n"
"\n"
"Package: *\n"
"Pin: release a=&codename-stable;-backports, o=Backports.org archive\n"
"Pin-Priority: 200\n"
"\n"
"Package: *\n"
"Pin: release a=&codename-stable;-sloppy, o=volatile.debian.org\n"
"Pin-Priority: 200"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8621
msgid "Execution of \"<literal>apt-get upgrade</literal>\" and \"<literal>apt-get dist-upgrade</literal>\" (or \"<literal>aptitude safe-upgrade</literal>\" and \"<literal>aptitude full-upgrade</literal>\" for <literal>squeeze</literal>) upgrades packages which were installed from <literal>stable</literal> archive using current <literal>stable</literal> archive and packages which were installed from other archives using current corresponding archive for all archives in the \"<literal>/etc/apt/sources.list</literal>\" file."
msgstr "L'excution de &nbsp;<literal>apt-get upgrade</literal>&nbsp; et &nbsp;<literal>apt-get dist-upgrade</literal>&nbsp;  (ou &nbsp;<literal>aptitude safe-upgrade</literal>&nbsp; et &nbsp;<literal>aptitude full-upgrade</literal>&nbsp; pour <literal>squeeze</literal>) met  niveau les paquet qui avaient t installs depuis l'archive <literal>stable</literal> en utilisant l'archive <literal>stable</literal> actuelle et les paquets qui avaient t installs depuis d'autres archives en utilisant l'archive actuelle correspondante pour toutes les archives figurant dans le fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/sources.list</literal>&nbsp;."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8624
msgid "Automatic download and upgrade of packages"
msgstr "Chargement et mise  niveau automatique de paquets"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8625
msgid "The <literal>apt</literal> package comes with its own cron script \"<literal>/etc/cron.daily/apt</literal>\" to support the automatic download of packages.  This script can be enhanced to perform the automatic upgrade of packages by installing the <literal>unattended-upgrades</literal> package. These can be customized by parameters in \"<literal>/etc/apt/apt.conf.d/02backup</literal>\" and \"<literal>/etc/apt/apt.conf.d/50unattended-upgrades</literal>\" as described in \"<literal>/usr/share/doc/unattended-upgrades/README</literal>\"."
msgstr "Le paquet <literal>apt</literal> est diffus avec son propre script d'vnements planifis (cron) &nbsp;<literal>/etc/cron.daily/apt</literal>&nbsp; afin de grer le tlchargement automatique de paquets. Ce script peut tre amlior afin d'effectuer la mise  niveau automatique des paquets en installant le paquet <literal>unattended-upgrades</literal>. Ceci peut tre personnalis  l'aide de paramtres se trouvant dans &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/apt.conf.d/02backup</literal>&nbsp; et &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/apt.conf.d/50unattended-upgrades</literal>&nbsp; comme dcrit dans &nbsp;<literal>/usr/share/doc/unattended-upgrades/README</literal>&nbsp;."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8626
msgid "The <literal>unattended-upgrades</literal> package is mainly intended for the security upgrade for the <literal>stable</literal> system.  If the risk of breaking an existing <literal>stable</literal> system by the automatic upgrade is smaller than that of the system broken by the intruder using its security hole which has been closed by the security update, you should consider using this automatic upgrade with configuration parameters as the following."
msgstr "Le paquet <literal>unattended-upgrades</literal> est principalement destin  des mises  jour de scurit des systmes <literal>stable</literal>. Si le risque de casser un systme <literal>stable</literal> existant par la mise  niveau automatique est plus faible que celui d'avoir un systme cass par un intrus utilisant une de ses failles de scurit qui a t ferme par une mise  jour de scurit, vous devriez envisager d'utiliser cette mise  niveau automatique avec les paramtres de configuration suivants&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8627
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"APT::Periodic::Update-Package-Lists \"1\";\n"
"APT::Periodic::Download-Upgradeable-Packages \"1\";\n"
"APT::Periodic::Unattended-Upgrade \"1\";"
msgstr ""
"APT::Periodic::Update-Package-Lists \"1\";\n"
"APT::Periodic::Download-Upgradeable-Packages \"1\";\n"
"APT::Periodic::Unattended-Upgrade \"1\";"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8630
msgid "If you are running an <literal>unstable</literal> system, you do not want to use the automatic upgrade since it certainly breaks system some day.  Even for such <literal>unstable</literal> case, you may still want to download packages in advance to save time for the interactive upgrade with configuration parameters as the following."
msgstr "Si vous faites tourner un systme <literal>unstable</literal>, vous ne devriez pas utiliser les mises  niveau automatiques car ceci cassera probablement votre systme un jour ou l'autre. Mme dans ce cas, avec <literal>unstable</literal>, vous pourrez tlcharger des paquets  l'avance afin de gagner du temps pour la mise  niveau interactive avec les paramtres de configuration suivants&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8631
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"APT::Periodic::Update-Package-Lists \"1\";\n"
"APT::Periodic::Download-Upgradeable-Packages \"1\";\n"
"APT::Periodic::Unattended-Upgrade \"0\";"
msgstr ""
"APT::Periodic::Update-Package-Lists \"1\";\n"
"APT::Periodic::Download-Upgradeable-Packages \"1\";\n"
"APT::Periodic::Unattended-Upgrade \"0\";"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8636
msgid "Limiting download bandwidth for APT"
msgstr "Diminuer la bande passante utilise par APT"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8637
msgid "If you want to limit the download bandwidth for APT to e.g. 800Kib/sec (=100kiB/sec), you should configure APT with its configuration parameter as the following."
msgstr "Si vous dsirez limiter la bande passante utilise par APT , par exemple, 800Kib/sec (=100kio/sec), vous devrez configurer APT avec son paramtre de configuration comme suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8638
#, no-wrap
msgid "APT::Acquire::http::Dl-Limit \"800\";"
msgstr "APT::Acquire::http::Dl-Limit \"800\";"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8641
msgid "Emergency downgrading"
msgstr "Retour d'urgence  une version prcdente (downgrade) "

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8643
msgid "Downgrading is not officially supported by the Debian by design.  It should be done only as a part of emergency recovery process.  Despite of this situation, it is known to work well in many incidents.  For critical systems, You should backup all important data on the system after the recovery operation and re-install the new system from the scratch."
msgstr "Le retour vers une version antrieure n'est pas officiellement gr par Debian dans sa conception. Ce ne devrait tre fait qu'en tant que partie d'un processus de rcupration d'urgence. Malgr cette situation, on sait que cela fonctionne bien pour de nombreux incidents. Avec les systmes critiques vous devrez effectuer un sauvegarde des donnes importantes du systme aprs l'opration de rcupration et rinstaller le nouveau systme depuis le dpart."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8645
msgid "You may be lucky to downgrade from newer archive to older archive to recover from broken system upgrade by manipulating <emphasis role=\"strong\">candidate version</emphasis> (see <xref linkend=\"_tweaking_candidate_version\"/>).  This is lazy alternative to tedious actions of many \"<literal>dpkg -i &lt;broken-package&gt;_&lt;old-version&gt;.deb</literal>\" commands (see <xref linkend=\"_rescue_with_the_dpkg_command\"/>)."
msgstr "Vous pouvez tre assez chanceux pour revenir en arrire depuis une archive plus rcente vers une archive plus ancienne afin de rcuprer une mise  jour du systme en manipulant la <emphasis role=\"strong\"> version candidate</emphasis> (voir <xref linkend=\"_tweaking_candidate_version\"/>). Cette mthode est un remplacement de paresseux des nombreuses et fastidieuses commandes &nbsp;<literal>dpkg -i &lt;paquet-cass&gt;_&lt;ancienne-version&gt;.deb</literal>&nbsp; (voir <xref linkend=\"_rescue_with_the_dpkg_command\"/>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8646
msgid "Search lines in the \"<literal>/etc/apt/sources.list</literal>\" file tracking <literal>unstable</literal> as the following."
msgstr "Recherchez les lignes du fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/sources.list</literal>&nbsp; permettant de suivre <literal>unstable</literal> ayant la forme suivante&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8647
#, no-wrap
msgid "deb http://ftp.us.debian.org/debian/ &codename-unstable; main contrib non-free"
msgstr "deb http://ftp.us.debian.org/debian/ &codename-unstable; main contrib non-free"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8648
msgid "Replace it with the following to track <literal>testing</literal>."
msgstr "Remplacez-la avec la suivante pour suivre <literal>testing</literal>&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8649
#, no-wrap
msgid "deb http://ftp.us.debian.org/debian/ &codename-testing; main contrib non-free"
msgstr "deb http://ftp.us.debian.org/debian/ &codename-testing; main contrib non-free"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8650
msgid "Set the \"<literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal>\" file as the following."
msgstr "Dfinissez comme suit le fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal>&nbsp;&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8651
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Package: *\n"
"Pin: release a=testing\n"
"Pin-Priority: 1010"
msgstr ""
"Package: *\n"
"Pin: release a=testing\n"
"Pin-Priority: 1010"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8654
msgid "Run \"<literal>apt-get dist-upgrade</literal>\" to force downgrading of packages across the system."
msgstr "Lancez &nbsp;<literal>apt-get dist-upgrade</literal>&nbsp; pour forcer l'installation  une version antrieure des paquets du systme."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8655
msgid "Remove this special \"<literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal>\" file after this emergency downgrading."
msgstr "Supprimez ce fichier spcial &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/preferences</literal>&nbsp; aprs ce retour en arrire d'urgence."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><tip><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8657
msgid "It is good idea to remove (not purge!) as much packages to minimize dependency problems.  You may need to manually remove and install some packages to get system downgraded.  Linux kernel, bootloader, udev, PAM, APT, and networking related packages and their configuration files require special attention."
msgstr "C'est une bonne ide de supprimer (sans purger) autant de paquets que possible afin de limiter les problmes de dpendances. Vous devrez peut-tre supprimer et installer manuellement un certain nombre de paquets afin de remettre le systme dans un tant antrieur. Le noyau de Linux, le gestionnaire d'amorage, udev, PAM, APT, et les paquets relatifs au rseau ainsi que leurs fichiers de configuration demandent une attention particulire."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8661
msgid "Who uploaded the package?"
msgstr "Qui a charg le paquet&nbsp;?"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8662
msgid "Although the maintainer name listed in \"<literal>/var/lib/dpkg/available</literal>\" and \"<literal>/usr/share/doc/package_name/changelog</literal>\" provide some information on \"who is behind the packaging activity\", the actual uploader of the package is somewhat obscure.  <literal>who-uploads</literal>(1) in the <literal>devscripts</literal> package identifies the actual uploader of Debian source packages."
msgstr "Bien que le nom du responsable figure dans &nbsp;<literal>/var/lib/dpkg/available</literal>&nbsp; et &nbsp;<literal>/usr/share/doc/package_name/changelog</literal>&nbsp; procure quelques informations sur &nbsp;qui se trouve derrire l'activit de construction des paquets&nbsp;, celui qui a rellement charg le paquet est un peu obscur. <literal>who-uploads</literal>(1) dans le paquet <literal>devscripts</literal> identifie celui qui a rellement charg les paquets sources Debian."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8665
msgid "The equivs package"
msgstr "Paquet equivs"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8666
msgid "If you are to compile a program from source to replace the Debian package, it is best to make it into a real local debianized package (<literal>*.deb</literal>) and use private archive."
msgstr "Si vous devez compiler un programme  partir de ses sources pour remplacer un paquet Debian, le mieux est d'en faire un paquet local rellement &nbsp;debianis&nbsp; (<literal>*.deb</literal>) et d'utiliser une archive prive."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8667
msgid "If you chose to compile a program from source and to install them under \"<literal>/usr/local</literal>\" instead, you may need to use <literal>equivs</literal> as a last resort to satisfy the missing package dependency."
msgstr "Si vous choisissez de compiler un programme depuis ses sources et de l'installer plutt sous &nbsp;<literal>/usr/local</literal>&nbsp;, vous pouvez avoir besoin d'utiliser <literal>equivs</literal> en dernier ressort pour satisfaire les dpendances des paquets manquants."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8668
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Package: equivs\n"
"Priority: extra\n"
"Section: admin\n"
"Description: Circumventing Debian package dependencies\n"
" This is a dummy package which can be used to create Debian\n"
" packages, which only contain dependency information."
msgstr ""
"Package: equivs\n"
"Priority: extra\n"
"Section: admin\n"
"Description: Passer outre les dpendances de paquets.\n"
" Ceci est paquet qui peut tre utilis pour crer des paquets Debian qui ne\n"
" contiennent que des informations sur les dpendances."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8676
msgid "Porting a package to the stable system"
msgstr "Porter un paquet vers le systme stable"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8677
msgid "For partial upgrades of the <literal>stable</literal> system, rebuilding a package within its environment using the source package is desirable.  This avoids massive package upgrades due to their dependencies."
msgstr "Pour des mises  niveau partielles du systme <literal>stable</literal>, il est souhaitable de reconstruire un paquet dans son environnement en utilisant le paquet source. Ceci vite des mises  niveau massives de paquets en raison de leurs dpendances."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8678
msgid "Add the following entries to the \"<literal>/etc/apt/sources.list</literal>\" of a <literal>stable</literal> system."
msgstr "Ajoutez les entres suivantes au fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/sources.list</literal>&nbsp; d'un systme <literal>stable</literal>&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8679
#, no-wrap
msgid "deb-src http://http.us.debian.org/debian unstable  main contrib non-free"
msgstr "deb-src http://http.us.debian.org/debian unstable  main contrib non-free"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8680
msgid "Install required packages for the compilation and download the source package as the following."
msgstr "Installez les paquets ncessaires  la compilation et tlchargez les sources comme suit:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8681
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"# apt-get update\n"
"# apt-get dist-upgrade\n"
"# apt-get install fakeroot devscripts build-essential\n"
"$ apt-get build-dep foo\n"
"$ apt-get source foo\n"
"$ cd foo*"
msgstr ""
"# apt-get update\n"
"# apt-get dist-upgrade\n"
"# apt-get install fakeroot devscripts build-essential\n"
"$ apt-get build-dep toto\n"
"$ apt-get source toto\n"
"$ cd toto*"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8687
msgid "Adjust installed packages if needed."
msgstr "Ajustez les paquets installs si ncessaire."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8688
msgid "Execute the following."
msgstr "Excutez ce qui suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8689 debian-reference.en.xmlt:30386
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ dch -i"
msgstr "$ dch -i"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8690
msgid "Bump package version, e.g. one appended with \"<literal>+bp1</literal>\" in \"<literal>debian/changelog</literal>\""
msgstr "Incrmentez la version du paquet, en ajoutant, par exemple &nbsp;<literal>+bp1</literal>&nbsp; dans &nbsp;<literal>debian/changelog</literal>&nbsp;"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8691
msgid "Build packages and install them to the system as the following."
msgstr "Construisez les paquets et installez-les sur le systme en faisant ce qui suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8692
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ debuild\n"
"$ cd ..\n"
"# debi foo*.changes"
msgstr ""
"$ debuild\n"
"$ cd ..\n"
"# debi toto*.changes"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8697
msgid "Proxy server for APT"
msgstr "Serveur mandataire (proxy) pour APT"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8698
msgid "Since mirroring whole subsection of Debian archive wastes disk space and network bandwidth, deployment of a local proxy server for APT is desirable consideration when you administer many systems on <ulink url=\"&lan;\">LAN</ulink>.  APT can be configure to use generic web (http) proxy servers such as <literal>squid</literal> (see <xref linkend=\"_other_network_application_servers\"/>) as described in <literal>apt.conf</literal>(5) and in \"<literal>/usr/share/doc/apt/examples/configure-index.gz</literal>\".  The \"<literal>$http_proxy</literal>\" environment variable can be used to override proxy server setting in the \"<literal>/etc/apt/apt.conf</literal>\" file."
msgstr "Comme effectuer le miroir complet d'une sous-section d'une archive Debian gaspille de l'espace disque et de la bande passante du rseau, il est souhaitable, lorsque vous administrez de nombreux systmes sur le <ulink url=\"&lan;\">LAN</ulink>, de mettre en uvre un serveur mandataire (&nbsp;proxy&nbsp;) local pour APT. APT peut tre configur pour utiliser un serveur mandataire web (http) gnrique comme <literal>squid</literal> (voir <xref linkend=\"_other_network_application_servers\"/>) tel que dcrit dans  <literal>apt.conf</literal>(5) et dans &nbsp;<literal>/usr/share/doc/apt/examples/configure-index.gz</literal>&nbsp;. La variable d'environnement &nbsp;<literal>$http_proxy</literal>&nbsp; peut tre utilise pour outrepasser le serveur mandataire dfinit dans le fichier &nbsp;<literal>/etc/apt/apt.conf</literal>&nbsp;."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8699
msgid "There are proxy tools specially for Debian archive.  You should check BTS before using them."
msgstr "Il y a des outils de proxy spcifiques pour l'archive Debian.  Vous devriez consulter le BTS avant de les installer."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><title>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8701
msgid "List of the proxy tools specially for Debian archive"
msgstr "Liste des outils de proxy spcifiques  l'archive Debian"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8729
msgid "caching proxy server for Debian archive files (compiled <ulink url=\"&ocaml;\">OCaml</ulink> program)"
msgstr "serveur proxy avec cache pour les fichiers de l'archive Debian (programme <ulink url=\"&ocaml;\">OCaml</ulink> compil)"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8737
msgid "Caching proxy for Debian package and source files (Perl program)"
msgstr "proxy avec cache pour les paquets et les fichiers source Debian (programme Perl)"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8745
msgid "Caching proxy for distribution of software packages (compiled C++ program)"
msgstr "proxy avec cache pour la distribution de paquets  de logiciel (programme C++ compil)"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><table><tgroup><tbody><row><entry>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8753
msgid "Bittorrent proxy for downloading Debian packages (Python program)"
msgstr "proxy bittorrent pour le tlchargement de paquets Debian (programme Python)"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><caution><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8760
msgid "When Debian reorganizes its archive structure, these specialized proxy tools tend to require code rewrites by the package maintainer and may not be functional for a while.  On the other hand, generic web (http) proxy servers are more robust and easier to cope with such changes."
msgstr "Lors que Debian rorganise la structure de son archive, ces outils de proxy spcialiss ont tendance  exiger que le code soit rcrit par le responsable du paquet et peuvent ne plus fonctionner pendant un certain temps. D'un autre ct, les serveur mandataires web (http) gnriques sont plus robustes et s'accommodent plus facilement de tel changements."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:8764
