#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19253
msgid "For <ulink url=\"&diskpartition;\">disk partition</ulink> configuration, although <literal>fdisk</literal>(8) has been considered standard, <literal>parted</literal>(8) deserves some attention.  \"Disk partitioning data\", \"partition table\", \"partition map\", and \"disk label\" are all synonyms."
msgstr "Bien que <literal>fdisk</literal>(8) ait t considr comme un standard pour la configuration de la <ulink url=\"&diskpartition;\">partition du disque partition</ulink>, mrite une certaine attention. &nbsp;Donnes de partition du disque&nbsp;, &nbsp;table de partition&nbsp; et &nbsp;tiquette de disque&nbsp; sont tous des synonymes."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19254
msgid "Most PCs use the classic <ulink url=\"&masterbootrecordmbr;\">Master Boot Record (MBR)</ulink> scheme to hold <ulink url=\"&diskpartitioning;\">disk partitioning</ulink> data in the first sector, i.e., <ulink url=\"&lba;\">LBA</ulink> sector 0 (512 bytes)."
msgstr "La plupart des PC utilisent le principe de l'<ulink url=\"&masterbootrecordmbr;\">Enregistrement Matre de dmarrage (MBR)</ulink> (&nbsp;Master Boot Record&nbsp;) pour enregistrer les donne de <ulink url=\"&diskpartitioning;\">partitiondu disque</ulink> sur le premier secteur, c'est--dire, le secteur 0 <ulink url=\"&lba;\">LBA</ulink> (512 octets)."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19256
msgid "Some new PCs with <ulink url=\"&extensiblefirmwareinterfaceefi;\">Extensible Firmware Interface (EFI)</ulink>, including Intel-based Macs, use <ulink url=\"&guidpartitiontablegpt;\">GUID Partition Table (GPT)</ulink> scheme to hold <ulink url=\"&diskpartitioning;\">disk partitioning</ulink> data not in the first sector."
msgstr "Certains PC rcent avec une <ulink url=\"&extensiblefirmwareinterfaceefi;\">Extensible Firmware Interface (EFI)</ulink>, ce qui comprend les Macs bass sur Intel, utilisent un principe de <ulink url=\"&guidpartitiontablegpt;\">GUID Partition Table (GPT)</ulink> pour enregistrer les donnes de <ulink url=\"&diskpartitioning;\">partitionnement du disque</ulink> ailleurs que sur le premier secteur."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:19258
msgid "Although <literal>fdisk</literal>(8) has been standard for the disk partitioning tool, <literal>parted</literal>(8) is replacing it."
msgstr "Alors que <literal>fdisk</literal>(8) a t l'outil standard departitionnement pour les disque, <literal>parted</literal>(8) le remplace maintenant."

