# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:22626
msgid "<literal>find</literal>(1) is used to select files for archive and copy commands (see <xref linkend=\"_idioms_for_the_archive\"/> and <xref linkend=\"_idioms_for_the_copy\"/>) or for <literal>xargs</literal>(1) (see <xref linkend=\"_repeating_a_command_looping_over_files\"/>).  This can be enhanced by using its command arguments."
msgstr "<literal>find</literal>(1) est utilis pour la slection de fichiers pour les commandes d'archive et de copie (voir <xref linkend=\"_idioms_for_the_archive\"/> et <xref linkend=\"_idioms_for_the_copy\"/>) ou pour <literal>xargs</literal>(1) (voir<xref linkend=\"_repeating_a_command_looping_over_files\"/>). Ceci peut tre amlior en utilisant ces paramtres de commande."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:22627
msgid "Basic syntax of <literal>find</literal>(1) can be summarized as the following."
msgstr "La syntaxe de base de <literal>find</literal>(1) peut tre rsume comme suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:22631
msgid "Its conditional arguments are evaluated from left to right."
msgstr "Ses paramtres conditionnels sont valus de gauche  droite."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:22636
msgid "This evaluation stops once its outcome is determined."
msgstr "L'valuation s'arrte lors que son rsultat est dtermin."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:22641
msgid "\"Logical <emphasis role=\"strong\">OR</emphasis>\" (specified by \"<literal>-o</literal>\" between conditionals) has lower precedence than \"logical <emphasis role=\"strong\">AND</emphasis>\" (specified by \"<literal>-a</literal>\" or nothing between conditionals)."
msgstr "Le &nbsp;<emphasis role=\"strong\">OU</emphasis> logique&nbsp; (indiqu par &nbsp;<literal>-o</literal>&nbsp; entre les lments conditionnels) a une plus faible priorit que le &nbsp;<emphasis role=\"strong\">ET</emphasis> logique&nbsp; (indiqu par &nbsp;<literal>-a</literal>&nbsp; ou rien entre lments conditionnels)."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:22646
msgid "\"Logical <emphasis role=\"strong\">NOT</emphasis>\" (specified by \"<literal>!</literal>\" before a conditional) has higher precedence than \"logical <emphasis role=\"strong\">AND</emphasis>\"."
msgstr "Le &nbsp;<emphasis role=\"strong\">NON</emphasis> logique&nbsp; (indiqu par &nbsp;<literal>!</literal>&nbsp; avant un lment conditionnel) a une priorit plus leve que le &nbsp;<emphasis role=\"strong\">ET</emphasis> logique&nbsp;."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:22651
msgid "\"<literal>-prune</literal>\" always returns logical <emphasis role=\"strong\">TRUE</emphasis> and, if it is a directory, searching of file is stopped beyond this point."
msgstr "&nbsp;<literal>-prune</literal>&nbsp; retourne toujours un <emphasis role=\"strong\">VRAI</emphasis> logique et, si c'est un rpertoire, la recherche de fichier est arrte au-del de ce point."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:22656
msgid "\"<literal>-name</literal>\" matches the base of the filename with shell glob (see <xref linkend=\"_shell_glob\"/>) but it also matches its initial \"<literal>.</literal>\" with metacharacters such as \"<literal>*</literal>\" and \"<literal>?</literal>\". (New <ulink url=\"&posix;\">POSIX</ulink> feature)"
msgstr "&nbsp;<literal>-name</literal>&nbsp; correspond  la base du nom de fichier avec les motifs gnriques de l'interprteur de commandes (voit <xref linkend=\"_shell_glob\"/>) mais il correspond aussi  son &nbsp;<literal>.</literal>&nbsp; de dbut avec des mta-caractres comme &nbsp;<literal>*</literal>&nbsp; et &nbsp;<literal>?</literal>&nbsp;. (Nouvelle fonctionnalit <ulink url=\"&posix;\">POSIX</ulink>)"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:22661
msgid "\"<literal>-regex</literal>\" matches the full path with emacs style <emphasis role=\"strong\">BRE</emphasis> (see <xref linkend=\"_regular_expressions\"/>) as default."
msgstr "&nbsp;<literal>-regex</literal>&nbsp; correspond au chemin complet par dfaut dans le style <emphasis role=\"strong\">BRE</emphasis> emacs (voir <xref linkend=\"_regular_expressions\"/>)."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:22666
msgid "\"<literal>-size</literal>\" matches the file based on the file size (value precedented with \"<literal>+</literal>\" for larger, precedented with \"<literal>-</literal>\" for smaller)"
msgstr "&nbsp;<literal>-size</literal>&nbsp; correspond au fichier en se basant sur la taille du fichier (valeur prcde de &nbsp;<literal>+</literal>&nbsp; pour plus grand et prcde de &nbsp;<literal>-</literal>&nbsp; pour plus petit)"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:22671
msgid "\"<literal>-newer</literal>\" matches the file newer than the one specified in its argument."
msgstr "&nbsp;<literal>-newer</literal>&nbsp; correspond au fichier plus rcent que celui indiqu comme paramtre."

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:22676
msgid "\"<literal>-print0</literal>\" always returns logical <emphasis role=\"strong\">TRUE</emphasis> and print the full filename (<ulink url=\"&nullterminated;\">null terminated</ulink>) on the standard output."
msgstr "&nbsp;<literal>-print0</literal>&nbsp; retourne toujours la valeur logique <emphasis role=\"strong\">VRAI</emphasis> et affiche sur la sortie standard le nom de fichier en entier (<ulink url=\"&nullterminated;\">termin par le caractre null</ulink>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:22680
msgid "<literal>find</literal>(1) is often used with an idiomatic style as the following."
msgstr "<literal>find</literal>(1) est souvent utilis dans un style idiomatique comme ce qui suit&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:22681
#, no-wrap
