# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><note><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26599
msgid "Please note most encoding systems share the same code with ASCII for the 7 bit characters.  But there are some exceptions. If you are converting old Japanese C programs and URLs data from the casually-called shift-JIS encoding format to UTF-8 format, use \"<literal>CP932</literal>\" as the encoding name instead of \"<literal>shift-JIS</literal>\" to get the expected results: <literal>0x5C</literal>  \"<literal>\\</literal>\" and <literal>0x7E</literal>  \"<literal>~</literal>\" .  Otherwise, these are converted to wrong characters."
msgstr "Veuillez remarquer que la plupart des systmes de codage partagent le mme code avec ASCII pour les caractres sur 7 bits. Mais il y a quelques exceptions, lors de la conversion de programmes C et des donnes d'URL anciens en japonais depuis ce qui est parfois appel format de codage shift-JIS vers le format UTF-8, utilisez &nbsp;<literal>CP932</literal>&nbsp; comme nom de codage plutt que &nbsp;<literal>shift-JIS</literal>&nbsp; afin d'obtenir le rsultat attendu&nbsp;: <literal>0x5C</literal>  &nbsp;<literal>\\</literal>&nbsp; et <literal>0x7E</literal>  &nbsp;<literal>~</literal>&nbsp;. Sinon, ils seront convertis vers les mauvais caractres."

