#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26775
msgid "An old western European Unix text file, \"<literal>u-file.txt</literal>\", stored in the latin1 (iso-8859-1) encoding can be edited simply with <literal>vim</literal> by the following."
msgstr "Un ancien fichier texte Unix d'Europe de l'ouest, &nbsp;<literal>u-file.txt</literal>&nbsp; enregistr dans le codage latin1 (iso-8859-1) peut tre dit avec <literal>vim</literal> de la manire suivante&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26776
#, no-wrap
msgid "$ vim u-file.txt"
msgstr "$ vim u-file.txt"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26777
msgid "This is possible since the auto detection mechanism of the file encoding in <literal>vim</literal> assumes the UTF-8 encoding first and, if it fails, assumes it to be latin1."
msgstr "Ceci est possible car le mcanisme d'auto-dtection du codage du fichier dans <literal>vim</literal> suppose d'abord que le codage est UTF-8 et, s'il choue, suppose qu'il est latin1."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:26778
msgid "An old Polish Unix text file, \"<literal>pu-file.txt</literal>\", stored in the latin2 (iso-8859-2) encoding can be edited with <literal>vim</literal> by the following."
msgstr "Un ancien fichier texte en polonais, &nbsp;<literal>pu-file.txt</literal>&nbsp;, enregistr avec le codage latin2 (iso-8859-2) peut tre dit avec <literal>vim</literal> de la manire suivante&nbsp;:"

