#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30785
msgid "<ulink url=\"&autoconf;\">Autoconf</ulink> is a tool for producing shell scripts that automatically configure software source code packages to adapt to many kinds of Unix-like systems using the entire GNU build system."
msgstr "<ulink url=\"&autoconf;\">Autoconf</ulink> est un outil destin  produire des scripts en shell qui configurent automatiquement un code source de logiciel pour l'adapter  de nombreux types de systmes &nbsp;Unix-like&nbsp; en utilisant l'ensemble du systme de construction GNU."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30786
msgid "<literal>autoconf</literal>(1) produces the configuration script \"<literal>configure</literal>\". \"<literal>configure</literal>\" automatically creates a customized \"<literal>Makefile</literal>\" using the \"<literal>Makefile.in</literal>\" template."
msgstr "<literal>autoconf</literal>(1) produit le script de configuration &nbsp;<literal>configure</literal>&nbsp;. &nbsp;<literal>configure</literal>&nbsp; cre automatiquement une &nbsp;<literal>Makefile</literal>&nbsp; en utilisant le patron &nbsp;<literal>Makefile.in</literal>&nbsp;."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30788
msgid "Compile and install a program"
msgstr "Compiler et installer un programme"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><warning><simpara>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><warning><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30790
msgid "Do not overwrite system files with your compiled programs when installing them."
msgstr "Ne pas craser les fichiers du systme avec les programmes que vous avez compils en les installant."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30792
msgid "Debian does not touch files in \"<literal>/usr/local/</literal>\" or \"<literal>/opt</literal>\".  So if you compile a program from source, install it into \"<literal>/usr/local/</literal>\" so it does not interfere with Debian."
msgstr "Debian ne touche pas aux fichiers se trouvant dans &nbsp;<literal>/usr/local/</literal>&nbsp; ou &nbsp;<literal>/opt</literal>&nbsp;. Donc, si vous compilez un programme depuis ses sources, installez-le dans &nbsp;<literal>/usr/local/</literal>&nbsp; de manire  ce qu'il n'interfre pas avec Debian."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30793
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ cd src\n"
"$ ./configure --prefix=/usr/local\n"
"$ make\n"
"$ make install # this puts the files in the system"
msgstr ""
"$ cd src\n"
"$ ./configure --prefix=/usr/loca\n"
"$ make\n"
"$ make install # cela met les fichiers dans le systme"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30799
msgid "Uninstall program"
msgstr "Dsinstaller un programme"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30800
msgid "If you have the original source and if it uses <literal>autoconf</literal>(1)/<literal>automake</literal>(1) and if you can remember how you configured it, execute as follows to uninstall the program."
msgstr "Si vous avez les sources d'origine et s'ils utilisent <literal>autoconf</literal>(1) et <literal>automake</literal>(1) et si vous-vous souvenez comment vous l'avez configur, excutez-le comme suit pour dsinstaller le programme&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30801
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"$ ./configure \"all-of-the-options-you-gave-it\"\n"
"# make uninstall"
msgstr ""
"$ ./configure &nbsp;toutes-les-options-que-vous-lui-avez-pass&nbsp;\n"
"# make uninstall"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30803
msgid "Alternatively, if you are absolutely sure that the install process puts files only under \"<literal>/usr/local/</literal>\" and there is nothing important there, you can erase all its contents by the following."
msgstr "Sinon, si vous tes absolument certain que le processus d'installation n'a mis des fichiers que sous &nbsp;<literal>/usr/local/</literal>&nbsp; et qu'il n'y a l rien d'important, vous pouvez supprimer tout son contenu avec&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30804
#, no-wrap
msgid "# find /usr/local -type f -print0 | xargs -0 rm -f"
msgstr "# find /usr/local -type f -print0 | xargs -0 rm -f"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30805
msgid "If you are not sure where files are installed, you should consider using <literal>checkinstall</literal>(8)  from the <literal>checkinstall</literal> package, which provides a clean path for the uninstall.  It now supports to create a Debian package with \"<literal>-D</literal>\" option."
msgstr "Si vous n'tes pas certain de l'emplacement o les fichiers ont t installs, vous devriez envisager d'utiliser <literal>checkinstall</literal>(8)  du paquet <literal>checkinstall</literal> qui fournit une voie propre pour la dsistallation. Il prend maintenant en charge la cration d'un paquet Debian  l'aide de l'option &nbsp;<literal>-D</literal>&nbsp;."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><title>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30809
msgid "Perl short script madness"
msgstr "Folie de courts scripts en Perl"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30810
msgid "Although any <ulink url=\"&awk;\">AWK</ulink> scripts can be automatically rewritten in <ulink url=\"&perl;\">Perl</ulink> using <literal>a2p</literal>(1), one-liner AWK scripts are best converted to one-liner Perl scripts manually."
msgstr "Bien que tous les scripts en <ulink url=\"&awk;\">AWK</ulink> puissent tre rcrits automatiquement en <ulink url=\"&perl;\">Perl</ulink> en utilisant <literal>a2p</literal>(1), il est plus facile de convertir manuellement les scripts AWK constitus d'une seule ligne en scripts Perl d'une seule ligne."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30811
msgid "Let's think following AWK script snippet."
msgstr "Regardons le bout de script AWK suivant&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30812
#, no-wrap
msgid "awk '($2==\"1957\") { print $3 }' |"
msgstr "awk '($2==\"1957\") { print $3 }' |"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30813
msgid "This is equivalent to any one of the following lines."
msgstr "Il est quivalent  l'une quelconque des lignes suivantes&nbsp;:"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30814
#, no-wrap
msgid "perl -ne '@f=split; if ($f[1] eq \"1957\") { print \"$f[2]\\n\"}' |"
msgstr "perl -ne '@f=split; if ($f[1] eq \"1957\") { print \"$f[2]\\n\"}' |"

# type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><screen>
#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30815
#, no-wrap
msgid "perl -ne 'if ((@f=split)[1] eq \"1957\") { print \"$f[2]\\n\"}' |"
msgstr "perl -ne 'if ((@f=split)[1] eq \"1957\") { print \"$f[2]\\n\"}' |"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30816
#, no-wrap
msgid "perl -ne '@f=split; print $f[2] if ( $f[1]==1957 )' |"
msgstr "perl -ne '@f=split; print $f[2] if ( $f[1]==1957 )' |"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30817
#, no-wrap
msgid "perl -lane 'print $F[2] if $F[1] eq \"1957\"' |"
msgstr "perl -lane 'print $F[2] if $F[1] eq \"1957\"' |"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><screen>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30818
#, no-wrap
msgid "perl -lane 'print$F[2]if$F[1]eq+1957' |"
msgstr "perl -lane 'print$F[2]if$F[1]eq+1957' |"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30819
msgid "The last one is a riddle.  It took advantage of following Perl features."
msgstr "La dernire est une devinette. Elle tire parti des fonctionnalits suivantes de Perl&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30823
msgid "The whitespace is optional."
msgstr "L'espace est optionnel."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30828
msgid "The automatic conversion exists from number to the string."
msgstr "Il existe une conversion automatique des nombres en chane de caractres."

#. type: Content of: <book><chapter><section><simpara>
#: debian-reference.en.xmlt:30832
msgid "See <literal>perlrun</literal>(1) for the command-line options.  For more crazy Perl scripts, <ulink url=\"&perlgolf;\">Perl Golf</ulink> may be interesting."
msgstr "Voir <literal>perlrun</literal>(1) pour les options de la ligne de commande. Pour des scripts en Perl plus fous, il peut tre intressant de consulter <ulink url=\"&perlgolf;\">Perl Golf</ulink>."

